title: Sunday at the Hotel with George
description: While attending the wedding of Blaisdell's daughter in a hotel. Peter inadvertently discovers some men with guns. They are there to rob the security boxes. So to make sure Peter doesn't do anything, the leader sends some of his men to the reception to make sure Peter doesn't and that no one goes down. Peter and Caine try to find a way to get to the lower floor.

title: Sacred Trust
description: When The Ancient sets out to commit suicide for the murder of a relative that he was sworn to protect, it is up to Caine to uncover the deception & prove to his friend that he did not break any sacred trust.

title: Force of Habit
description: Peter and his latest partner, Marty Stramm, are tracking a gun dealer trading dangerously advanced weapons. Stramm is a good cop, but the stress of the job is making him abusive towards his wife, Emily. Kwai-Chang offers Emily support, and her self-esteem is boosted as he starts to teach her kung fu, but Stramm reacts explosively and beats her during an argument. Peter and Stramm succeed in apprehending the gun dealer, but Stramm is horrified when his son, Billy, appears outside the police station with a gun, determined to protect his mother. Kwai-Chang and Peter manage to prevent a shootout, and Stramm quits the force rather than continue to endanger his family.

title: Challenge
description: Tan, the renegade Shaolin Monk who destroyed the temple where Caine lived with Peter which led to them being separated for 15 years, who would become a crime boss whom Caine encountered and defeated some months ago returns. He then sends Caine a message which Caine interprets as a challenge. He then has his man, Chan grab the Ancient. Caine and Peter then go to where Tan is and the challenge begins.

title: Disciple
description: Kwai Chan takes on a new disciple. His new student is already very adept at martial arts, but Kaine hopes to teach him martial arts is more than just fighting. Peter tries to track down illegal street fighting /gambling.

title: Dragon's Eye
description: A man takes his daughter, who is sick, to Caine to see if he can help her. Caine makes something for her, and for awhile it seems to work but she soon becomes sick. Caine needs more of the main ingredient, a flower which at this time of the year grows in area taken over by a mad vet. Caine manages to find the flower and when confronted by the man, convinces him to let him go but Peter arrives and they have to go, leaving the flowers behind. They return for the flowers but the man has already laid a trap.

title: Blind Eye
description: Annie Blaisdell asks Caine to accompany her when she goes to meet someone. After meeting him, she's attacked. Blaisdell's upset with Caine. Caine goes to see Annie and gets her to give him a description of the one who attacked her. Along with Peter, they find him and find out why they attacked her.

title: Straitjacket
description: Karen Kaden is a young woman who is being harassed by a group of men who want her to appear insane. These men constantly threaten her and recently wrecked her apartment. Karen asked the police for help, but she had no evidence. Even her apartment was restored to normal by the time she returned from the police station. No one will believe her except Kung Fu teacher Kwai Chang Caine.

title: Shaman
description: An Indian mystic accused of murder enlists Kwai Chang Caine to prove his innocence.

title: I Never Promised You a Rose Garden
description: Alicia Wright, a student in Kwai Chang Caine's kung fu class, has a problem. Her grandmother, with whom she has lived since the death of her parents, has stopped tending her rose garden, a garden, which was very precious and important to her. Alicia senses that as the garden dies, so does her grandmother. Caine tries to help by taking care of the garden.

title: Return of the Shadow Assassin
description: Peter becomes the center of an investigation when four women he knows are found dead under unusual circumstances. He thinks that somehow the deaths are related to a series of vivid dreams he's been having.

title: May I Ride with You
description: Kwai Chan wants to understand his son better, he spends the day with Peter to see what he does at work. Peter's reluctant, but he lets his father follow him along. Among their encounters, a youth in the foster care program, a woman who is wants to jump off a building because she thinks she'll lose custody of her child, and a group of Kwai Chan's enemies who pop up and start attacking them at various times.

title: An Ancient Lottery
description: When The Ancient wins the lottery, the entire community gathers outside his home for their turn to appeal to his generosity - but the bad guys, who are also after his money, are not so patient.

title: Temple
description: Caine and Peter return to the site where the Temple was. And they encounter some people who were involved with it's destruction.

title: Only the Strong Survive
description: Peter goes undercover at a Martial Arts tournament to look for someone who was kidnapped. He asks Caine to show him a move that can impress. When Peter does it, the owner recognizes it. It seems he and Caine meet 10 years ago and it was not a good confrontation.

title: The Bardo
description: An accident sends Peter in a coma; stuck at the Bardo, a purgatory between life & death, he confronts his demons and his life-long abandonment issues as Caine joins him in the battle for his soul but is it too late to save Peter?

title: The Possessed
description: The Church is trying to exorcise a man who is possessed. However, something goes wrong and the demon starts to possess other people.

title: Warlord
description: A Chinese warlord comes to town looking for Caine. When he fails to find him, he goes looking for Peter so he goes to the station. The man is very ego maniacal that pushes people around and he butts heads with people at the station especially with Frank. Eventually he finds Caine and tells him, he wants him to help his father who is sick. Caine tells him he will see him when he can. The man goes out and runs into Frank and that's when Frank calls him out and they got at it and Frank ends up in the hospital. Caine later tries to help the man's father but he's so sick Caine can't do anything. When his father died, the warlord blames Caine and demands that Caine battle him to the death.

title: The Innocent
description: Caine's been summoned for jury duty where the case involves a homeless man accused of killing a businessman and robbing him. But the defendant claims the man was already dead when he came across him. Peter decides to go to the trial and as the prosecution makes its case, Caine gives Peter a look which is his way of telling him there were some anomalies in the prosecution's case. Peter has the forensic evidence reviewed and learns that the medical examiner made some oversights. Peter learns that the victim was heavily insured and the beneficiary is his business so the one who has a lot to gain is the man's partner. Peter tries to check him out but couldn't get anything. In the meantime the jury foreman was approached by a man who threatens his family if they don't come back with a guilty verdict. At deliberation Caine hangs the jury. Caine senses something wrong with the foreman and tells Peter that his family could be in danger.

title: Magic Trick
description: Peter tries to save a beautiful woman who is under the hypnotic spell of a stage illusionist, but she resists him. Caine brings his own brand of magic to the nightclub as he battles the mentalist to deprogram the woman.

title: Kundela
description: Aborigines cast a retaliation death spell upon Peter's latest flame, an Australian tennis player whose entrepreneur father plans to build a mall on their sacred burial land.

title: Sunday at the Museum with George
Dragonswing II
description: Some men take Caine and he leaves Peter a clue. When Peter tries to decipher the clue, Rykker the mercenary friend of Caine shows up and offers to help. He then asks Steadman to help who reluctantly agrees.

title: Retribution
description: When Blaisdell is accused of a crime he claims he didn't commit. He turns to Caine for help. He suspects it might have something to do with his life as a mercenary. So he asks Caine to take a great risk.

title: May I Walk with You
description: Peter wants to see what Kwai Chan does during the day. So he spends the day following his father and helping him as he tries to aide others.

title: Gunfighters
description: In the early 20th century Caine stands up to a man who is terrorizing a town. Also in the town is his wife and their son. Caine only has the drunken deputy and Cheyenne Bodie to help him. One night the man comes into Caine's home and grabs his wife and son and shoots Caine. While Caine is near death, he transports himself to the present and seeks out his grandson--the present day Kwai Chang Caine. When he finds him, he tells him that he has to help his grandmother and father. So Caine goes and along with Bodie and the deputy go to rescue them.

title: Chinatown Murder Mystery: The Case of the Poisoned Hand
The Sacred Chalice of I-Ching
description: Kwai-Chang Caine and his son travel to France along with Bennett to attempt to save the eponymous Chalice from a neo-Nazi archeologist.

title: Deadly Fashion
description: Caine surprises Peter, as he joins him in his undercover investigation in the fashion world, posing as Gaston, a famed French designer complete with flashy clothes & gaudy glasses, while his son acts as bodyguard for a supermodel.

title: Flying Fists of Fury II
description: To protect a celebrity from men who want to kill him, Peter goes undercover on a movie set as an obnoxious and arrogant movie star whose striking resemblance to Caine's son is uncanny.

title: Brotherhood of the Bell
description: Caine leaves and all signs appear that he will not return. Peter tries to find out where he went. Later a man shows up claiming to be Caine's half-brother and thinks he knows where Caine is going. So they go to try and help him.

title: The First Temple
description: Caine and Peter go back in time to the Shaolin Temple and meet their ancestor Kwai Chang. And they teach him and the other monks kung fu to defend themselves when they're about to be attacked.

title: Shaolin Shot
description: Peter doubts himself because he did not react when an intruder acted out at the precinct. He transfers his anger onto Caine who leaves town. Peter joins a hockey team to apprehend the man who hurt Kelly's brother.

title: Dragon's Lair
description: The 101 Precinct cops start acting erratic when they are under the spell of an ancient Chinese board game that a group of kids discovered in an haunted house and started playing. It is up to Caine to break the curse.
